'''K<U+00E1>z<U+00ED>m Abdulakim''' (also transliterated in [[Romanian language|Romanian]] as: '''Kiazim Abdulachim''', '''Kiazim Abdulakim''' or '''Chiazim Abdulachim''') was a [[Crimean Tatar]] [[hero]] of the [[Romanian Armed Forces|Romanian Army]] who lost his life in the [[summer]] of [[1917]] during the [[Battle of M<U+0103>r<U+0103><U+015F>e<U+015F>ti]] in the [[World War I]].{{sfn|Agi-Amet|1999}}{{sfn|Scurtu|2011}}

'''[[Second Lieutenant]] K<U+00E1>z<U+00ED>m Abdulakim''' was the [[brother]] of [[lawyer]] [[Selim Abdulakim]] who, between the two wars, became a leading politician of the [[Crimean Tatars in Romania]], [[Deputy Mayor]] of [[Constanta]] and a Member of the [[Romanian Parliament]].{{sfn|Agi-Amet|1999}} K<U+00E1>z<U+00ED>m<U+2019>s [[sister]] <U+015E>efika, also known as Sapiye, was the wife of the beloved [[Crimean Tatar]] [[poet]] [[Mehmet Niyazi|Memet Niyaziy]].{{sfn|Agi-Amet|1999}}{{sfn|Romania Libera|2007}}

As recognition of his extreme devotion to duty and ultimate sacrifice, in [[Dobruja]] was founded ''Second Lieutenant K<U+00E1>z<U+00ED>m Abdulakim Cultural and Sports Association''{{sfn|Scurtu|2013|p:214}} and a street in downtown [[Constanta]]{{sfn|Strazi}}{{sfn|Google Maps}} was named in K<U+00E1>z<U+00ED>m<U+2019>s honor.

